abstract: Leading homebuilder Lennar reports third-quarter earnings of $223.3 million, up from $177.8 million year earlier, due to improving housing market.
lead_paragraph: Lennar’s results for its third fiscal quarter beat analysts’ estimates as it delivered more homes and new orders rose in an improving housing market.

headline.main: Improving Housing Market Bolsters Lennar’s Bottom Line
